Higher even than that of either of these was the lineage of the Junii Silani, the only direct descendants of Augustus⁸ save Nero himself ; and the onslaught on this family commenced by Agrippinal was carried on by Nero in 817, an. 64, by a private trial, resulting in the death of its chief living representative ⁸.
